hieved\n\nRule: No Racism No genuine racism, including slurs, non-factual content, and general unfounded bigotry.\n\nReality: Slurs are constant, I tried to give examples, but my post kept being auto deleted by site automation\n\nSo either you need to change the rules or start cracking down. Why even have a rules section if everyone constantly breaks them? If I go into a Discord and it's got a bunch of leftist lunacy like \"no transphobia\" I know 100% if I even imply something that goes against their ideology, I'm getting kicked out of there in a nanosecond. So I just keep my mouth shut on any place like Reddit or a Discord.\n\nMods, enforce the rules or do something please.", "author": "StaticNoise2", "created": 1776614943182, "profile_picture": "iPSqIDDiZC8M", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Badfinz_FL", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "The rules of this site vs the reality", "last_comment_created": 1776628210538, "content": "<p>Rule: Patriots is not a catch-all free speech community for the political right.</p>\n<p>Reality: At the moment it is either a subverted place with redditors, doomers, feds or critical thinking lacking dissident right where you can do no good ever, and every time anything good happens, the goal post moves.</p>\n<p>Rule: We are explicitly for supporters of MAGA and Trump, and we facilitate a platform where those users specifically can speak their mind. Be here for MAGA and Trump</p>\n<p>Reality: This place is as anti-Trump in the past 4+ months as Reddit nearly.</p>\n<p>Rule: We\u2019re a community for those who want to Make America Great Again. If your purpose here is to push other unrelated or tangential agendas, you\u2019re not welcome.</p>\n<p>Reality: You could 